  "text": "Spectral-domain OCT (Zeiss Cirrus (Carl Zeiss Meditec, Dublin, CA, USA), models 4000 and 5000, for OCT thickness and macular volume; Spectralis (Heidelberg Engineering, Heidelberg, Germany) for choroidal thickness) was performed monthly over 12 months to assess mean changes in central foveal thickness (CFT) and macular volume from baseline over time up to month 12. Additional assessments included the proportion of patients with no OCT evidence of intraretinal or subretinal fluid from CNV at month 12 and choroidal thickness at months 3 and 12. Choroidal thickness was measured by enhanced depth imaging-OCT. [CITATION_1] Measurements were taken at the fovea and at locations 1.5-mm temporal, nasal, superior, and inferior to the center of the fovea.",
